BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 70.08000000000001 600 Td (Chapter 3: Finding Profitable Products) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (The best products to sell are lightweight, unbreakable, and priced 15-50 dollars.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Avoid categories dominated by major brands like Apple or Nike.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Look for products with high demand but moderate competition on Amazon.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Use the Amazon Best Sellers list to identify hot-selling categories.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (A product selling at least ten units per day per competitor indicates good demand.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Check the number of reviews on top listings. Under 500 reviews means opportunity.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Avoid seasonal products unless you plan to sell multiple seasonal items.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Products with room for improvement based on negative reviews are ideal.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Read competitor one and two star reviews to find what customers want fixed.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Tools like Jungle Scout and Helium 10 provide sales estimates for products.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Never choose a product based on gut feeling alone. Use data to decide.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Start with one product, learn the process, then expand to more items.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (3) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
