BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 54.72 600 Td (Chapter 8: Writing Effective Bullet Points) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Amazon gives you five bullet points to highlight your product benefits.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Lead each bullet with a capitalized benefit header followed by details.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Focus on benefits to the customer, not just features of the product.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Instead of saying waterproof material say never worry about rain ruining it.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Include keywords naturally in your bullets for search visibility.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Address common customer objections and concerns in your bullets.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Mention what is included in the package so buyers know exactly what they get.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Keep bullets readable: two to three lines each, not massive paragraphs.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Use the first bullet for your strongest selling point since most people read it.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Include size, material, and compatibility information buyers need to decide.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Study top competitors bullets and note what they emphasize.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Well-written bullets can double your conversion rate from visitors to buyers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (8) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
