BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 108.48 600 Td (Chapter 9: Amazon SEO Basics) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Amazon SEO is about ranking your product higher in Amazon search results.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (The Amazon algorithm is called A9 and it prioritizes products that sell well.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Include your main keyword in the product title for maximum search visibility.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Use all available backend search term fields with relevant keywords.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Do not repeat words that already appear in your title in backend terms.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Sales velocity is the strongest ranking factor: more sales means higher rank.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Click-through rate matters: great images and titles get more clicks.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Conversion rate matters: good descriptions and reviews turn clicks into sales.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Use competitor product titles for keyword research inspiration.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Tools like Helium 10 Cerebro show which keywords competitors rank for.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Price competitively at launch to generate initial sales velocity.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Amazon SEO is an ongoing process. Monitor and adjust keywords monthly.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 213.6 30 Td (9) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
