BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 93.12 600 Td (Chapter 10: FBA vs FBM Explained) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (FBA means Fulfillment by Amazon: you send inventory, they store and ship it.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (FBM means Fulfillment by Merchant: you store inventory and ship orders yourself.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (FBA products get the Prime badge which dramatically increases sales.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Amazon handles all customer service and returns for FBA items.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (FBA fees include storage fees and fulfillment fees based on size and weight.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (FBM has lower fees but you handle packing, shipping, and customer service.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (FBM makes sense for large, heavy, or slow-selling items.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (FBA makes sense for small, lightweight items that sell consistently.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Most successful sellers use FBA because Prime customers spend more.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Long-term storage fees apply to FBA items stored over 365 days.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (You can use both methods simultaneously for different products.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (For beginners, FBA is recommended to focus on sourcing rather than shipping.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (10) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
