BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 100.80000000000001 600 Td (Chapter 11: Pricing Strategies) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (Price your product competitively by analyzing the top ten sellers in your niche.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Factor in all costs: product cost, shipping to Amazon, FBA fees, and advertising.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Aim for at least 30 percent profit margin after all Amazon fees.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Use the Amazon FBA Revenue Calculator to estimate your actual profit per unit.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Consider launching at a lower price initially to generate reviews and sales velocity.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Raise your price gradually once you have reviews and consistent sales.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Monitor competitor prices regularly and adjust to stay competitive.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Avoid price wars that drive profits to zero for everyone in the category.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Bundle products together to create unique offers that cannot be price-compared.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Offer coupons and deals through Amazon to boost conversion without lowering list price.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Test different price points to find the sweet spot for maximum profit.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Remember: the cheapest price does not always win. Value and reviews matter more.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (11) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
