BT 0 g /F2 16 Tf 89.28 600 Td (Chapter 13: Amazon PPC Ads Basics) Tj ET
q 0 G 1 w 60 585 m 372 585 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 560 Td (PPC means Pay Per Click: you only pay when someone clicks your ad.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 538 Td (Amazon advertising puts your product at the top of search results.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 516 Td (Start with Sponsored Products automatic campaigns to discover keywords.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 494 Td (Set a daily budget of ten to twenty dollars when starting out.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 472 Td (Let automatic campaigns run for two weeks to gather keyword data.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 450 Td (Then create manual campaigns targeting the keywords that converted to sales.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 428 Td (Your advertising cost of sale \(ACoS\) should ideally be below 30 percent.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 406 Td (Negative keywords prevent your ads from showing for irrelevant searches.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 384 Td (Bid higher on keywords that are converting well and lower on poor performers.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 362 Td (Product targeting ads show your listing on competitor product pages.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 340 Td (Advertising is essential at launch but can be reduced once organic rank improves.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 50 318 Td (Think of PPC as an investment in ranking, not just a cost of doing business.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F1 10 Tf 211.2 30 Td (13) Tj ET

endstream
